sc0 ls0 ws0">suggestions.&quot; </div><div class="t m3b xb3 h23 y574 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Many people treat the Ten </div><div class="t m442 xf h23 y575 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Commandments as a set of laws that do not have relevance to us </div><div class="t m127 xf h23 y576 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">today. Some argue that the attempt to obey the Ten Commandments </div><div class="t m1a0 x53 h23 y577 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">amounts to legalism. They think the law of love demands that we </div><div class="t m33b x53 h23 y578 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sometimes act contrary to the Ten Commandments. </div><div class="t m2d7 x35 h23 y579 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Some Christians declare that the Ten Commandments were nailed </div><div class="t m18a xf h23 y57a ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to the cross. They assert that the Old Testament ten-commandment </div><div class="t m40 xf h23 y57b ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">law is no longer binding. </div><div class="t m443 x35 h23 y57c ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Others believe that their works of obedience to the laws of God and </div><div class="t m164 xf h23 y57d ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the policies of the church will somehow improve their standing with </div><div class="t m444 x53 h23 y57e ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God. They believe that God&apos;s grace and our faith are necessary, but </div><div class="t m40 xf h23 y57f ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that our works are part of the means by which we are saved. </div><div class="t m150 xe h23 y580 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Has God always had a law that He has required His created beings </div><div class="t m99 xf h23 y581 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to obey? What is the relationship between the Ten Commandments </div><div class="t m43 x53 h23 y582 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and salvation by faith in Jesus Christ? </div><div class="t m445 x6e h23 y53a ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">38 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.00000